title: Campaigning ramps up ahead of Ireland's divisive referendum
text:
Campaigning ramps up ahead of Ireland's divisive referendum Wednesday, May 23, 2018 - 01:48
Ireland's referendum on liberalising abortion laws is just days away. The country has one of the world's strictest prohibitions on the procedure - and the subject has long divided the nation. Julian Satterthwaite reports.
